11 Sec. 31509a. (1) The department shall establish a staggered
12 registration process that meets all of the following conditions:
13 (a) Is divided into 5 rounds, with the first round of
14 registrations beginning 6 months after the effective date of the
15 2025 amendatory act that added this section.
16 (b) Registers 1/5 of all owners of dams in this state each
17 round.
18 (c) Identifies the owners of dams that are subject to
19 registration in each round based on hazard potential classification
20 and other relevant considerations.
21 (2) Subject to subsection (1), an owner shall register all
22 dams owned by the owner with the department on a form and in a
23 manner prescribed by the department. The application for a
24 registration under this section must include all of the following
25 information:
26 (a) Proof of ownership of the dam.
27 (b) An asset management plan for all dams owned by the owner,
28 that includes all of the following information:
29 (i) An inventory of all dam assets.
