20 capacity shall must meet the following minimum criteria:
21 (a) Low hazard potential dams shall must be capable of passing
22 the 100-year flood, or the flood of record, whichever is greater.
23 (b) Significant hazard potential dams shall must be capable of
24 passing the 200-year half probable maximum flood, or the flood of
25 record, whichever is greater.
26 (c) High hazard potential dams , less than 40 feet in height,
27 as measured from the 200-year design flood elevation to the lowest
28 downstream toe elevation, shall be capable of passing the 200-year
29 flood, or the flood of record, whichever is greater.
RMH H04314'25 (H-4) k1iz8v

20
1 (d) High hazard potential dams, 40 feet or greater in height,
2 as measured from the 200-year design flood elevation to the lowest
3 downstream toe elevation, shall must be capable of passing the half
4 probable maximum flood, . The half probable maximum flood criterion
5 may be reduced to not less than the 200-year flood, with proper
6 documentation evidencing a failure of a dam under half probable
7 maximum flood conditions will not cause additional flood damage or
8 loss of life.or the flood of record, whichever is greater.
9 (d) (e) Spillway design capacity shall must not be less than
10 the flood of record.
11 (2) Freeboard shall must be considered when determining
12 spillway capacity.
13 (3) If a dam cannot pass the design flood, an auxiliary
14 additional spillway capacity must be provided. The owner must
15 document, to the satisfaction of the department, that the dam has
16 sufficient spillway capacity, and that proper means are available
17 to operate the spillway or spillways during the design flood.
18 (4) The criteria described under subsection (1) may be reduced
19 in accordance with a site-specific, consequence-based, or risk-
20 based inflow design flood study completed in a manner approved by
21 the department.
22 Sec. 31517. (1) Except for minor projects authorized pursuant
23 to under section 31513, the owner shall do both of the following:
24 (a) Within Not later than 10 days after the completion of a
25 new, reconstructed, enlarged, repaired, or altered dam, notify the
26 department of its completion.
27 (b) Within Not later than 20 days after submitting the notice
28 of completion, file with the department as-built plans and a
29 statement signed by a licensed professional engineer certifying
RMH H04314'25 (H-4) k1iz8v

21
1 that certifies that the project was constructed in conformance with
2 plans and specifications approved by the department.
3 (2) The department shall inspect the project and shall provide
4 the owner with written notice of final approval after the project
5 is completed if the project is determined to have been completed in
6 accordance with approved plans, specifications, and permit
7 conditions. The department may also inspect the project during
8 construction of the project.
9 (3) If the project is determined not to be completed in
10 accordance with approved plans, and specifications approved by the
11 department specifications, and permit conditions described under
12 subsection (2), the department shall provide notice to the
13 permittee as to the specific reasons the department determines the
14 project not to be completed in accordance with those the plans,
15 specifications, or permit conditions. The department may then take
16 enforcement action as provided in this part.
17 (4) Nothing in this act is construed to relieve an owner of
18 the legal duties, obligations, or liabilities incident to the
19 ownership or operation of a dam or impoundment.
20 Sec. 31517a. (1) An owner shall prepare and keep current
21 operations and maintenance records for each dam owned by the owner.
22 The operations and maintenance records must, at a minimum, contain
23 all of the following:
24 (a) A brief description of the major elements of the dam.
25 (b) Operation procedures during normal and high flows.
26 (c) Emergency action plans.
27 (d) Copies of recent inspection reports submitted to the
28 department under section 31518.
29 (e) Maintenance work order procedures.
