1 (f) Sample maintenance and inspection forms.
2 (g) Key contact information.
3 (2) An owner shall prepare and keep current a surveillance and
4 monitoring plan for each dam owned by the owner.
5 (3) An owner shall maintain all of the records described under
6 this section and make the records available to the department on
7 request.
8 Sec. 31518. (1) An owner shall submit to the department
9 inspection reports prepared by a licensed professional engineer
10 that evaluate the condition of the dam. The inspection report shall
11 must be submitted as follows:
12 (a) Not less than once every 3 years year for high hazard
13 potential dams.
14 (b) Not less than once every 4 2 years for significant hazard
15 potential dams.
16 (c) Not less than once every 5 years for low hazard potential
17 dams.
18 (2) The department shall determine the hazard potential
19 classification of for all dams and shall establish an inspection
20 schedule. The department shall notify the owner of each dam's
21 hazard potential classification, the effective date of each hazard
22 potential classification, and each dam's hazard potential history.
23 Not later than 30 days after the department's notice of a dam's
24 hazard potential classification under this subsection is received
25 by the owner, the owner shall provide the department with
26 information regarding how the owner will meet the requirements of
27 the dam's hazard potential classification, including, but not
28 limited to, spillway capacity, emergency action plan, inundation
29 mapping requirements, and an inspection schedule. An inspection
RMH H04314'25 (H-4) k1iz8v

23
1 schedule shall developed under this subsection must require annual
2 submission of inspection reports for approximately 1/3 of all high
3 hazard potential dams, 1/4 1/2 of all significant hazard potential
4 dams, and 1/5 of all low hazard potential dams. The department
5 shall notify the owners in writing when inspection reports are due.
6 The department may order additional inspection reports following an
7 event or change in condition that could threaten a dam.
8 (3) An inspection report required by this section shall must
9 include, at a minimum, all of the following:
10 (a) An evaluation of the dam's condition, spillway capacity,
11 operational adequacy, and structural integrity.
12 (b) A determination of whether deficiencies exist that could
13 lead to the failure of the dam.
14 (c) Recommendations for maintenance, repair, and alterations
15 of a dam as are necessary to eliminate any deficiencies.
16 (d) A schedule to address deficiencies that is approved by the
17 department. An owner violates this part if the owner fails to
18 address deficiencies in accordance with the schedule approved under
19 this subdivision.
20 (e) An assessment of the appropriateness of the current hazard
21 potential classification established under subsection (1) taking
22 into consideration the current conditions that exist downstream of
23 the dam. An assessment under this subdivision must consider
24 conditions related to damage as identified under a significant
25 hazard potential dam classification and serious damage as
26 identified under a high hazard potential dam classification that
27 might have changed since the effective date of the current hazard
28 classification established under subsection (1).
29 (f) An assessment of operations and maintenance based on the
