6 action being taken in response to an emergency condition.
7 Sec. 31521. (1) The department may issue to an owner a written
8 emergency orders as provided in this section. The department may,
9 by written notice, order an owner order that requires the owner to
10 immediately repair, draw down, breach, remove, or cease operation
11 of a dam where a if the dam is in imminent danger of failure and or
12 is causing or threatening to cause harm to public health, safety,
13 welfare, property, or the natural resources or the public trust in
14 those natural resources.
15 (2) If an owner fails to comply with an emergency order under
16 subsection (1), or is unavailable to or unable to cannot be
17 contacted, then the department may undertake immediate repair,
18 drawdown, breaching, removal, or cessation of operation, as may be
19 necessary to alleviate the danger. , and The department may recover
20 from the owner the costs incurred in a civil action. commenced in a
21 court of competent jurisdiction. The department may terminate an
22 emergency order upon on a determination in writing that all
23 necessary emergency actions have been complied with by the owner
24 and that an emergency no longer exists.
