12 public trust in those natural resources.
13 (5) (3) Upon Not later than 15 days after the issuance of an
14 emergency order under subsection (1), the department shall provide
15 the owner with an opportunity for a hearing pursuant to under the
16 administrative procedures act of 1969. within 15 days of the date
17 of its issuance. The department may proactively schedule a hearing
18 under this subsection, but the owner shall submit a petition to
19 request the hearing within 15 days after the issuance of an order
20 under this section before a hearing can be held. At the hearing,
21 the department shall determine, based on information and fact, if
22 the emergency order shall must be continued, modified, or suspended
23 as necessary to protect public health, safety, welfare, property,
24 or natural resources or the public trust in those natural
25 resources.
26 (6) A hearing held under subsection (5) does not preclude the
27 owner or department from immediately taking action as necessary to
