12 Sec. 31528a. (1) The dam safety emergency fund is created
13 within the state treasury. The state treasurer may receive money or
14 other assets from any source for deposit into the fund. The state
15 treasurer shall direct the investment of the fund and credit to the
16 fund interest and earnings from fund investments. Money in the fund
17 at the end of the fiscal year remains in the fund and does not
18 lapse to the general fund. The department is the administrator of
19 the fund for auditing purposes.
20 (2) On appropriation, the department shall expend money from
21 the fund to take remedial or corrective actions that remove or
22 reduce significant safety risks posed by dams when an owner is
23 unable or unwilling to take remedial or corrective action. The
24 department and the department of attorney general may recover costs
25 expended from the fund under this subsection from an owner.
26 Recovered costs must be deposited in the fund.
27 (3) As used in this section and section 31528b, "fund" means
28 the dam safety emergency fund created under subsection (1).
29 Sec. 31528b. (1) The department shall establish a dam risk
RMH H04314'25 (H-4) k1iz8v

32
1 reduction grant program as provided in this section.
2 (2) The program must provide grants to owners to complete any
3 of the following projects:
4 (a) Repair or alteration of a dam.
5 (b) Removal of a dam.
6 (c) Scoping and engineering plans associated with any of the
7 actions described in subdivisions (a) and (b).
8 (3) An owner shall apply to the program on a form and in a
9 manner prescribed by the department. To be eligible to receive a
10 grant from the program, the owner must be able to contribute
11 matching funds of at least 10%.
12 (4) As used in this section, "program" means the dam risk
13 reduction grant program created under subsection (1).
